title: Trip to Gagganchukki falls
content: Had a nice trip to this beautiful waterfalls with my friends around 100km from bengaluru, we hired a car and go there, the drive experience is also great, must visit place, prefer morning timings for beautiful weather.

title: Funday at Lal Bagh
content: I travelled to lalbagh with my college friend from HSR Layout, first we took a bus from NIFT College to Banashankari Bus Stop, then a metro from there to lalbagh, it took as around 1 hour to reach there. It was a beautiful place, there was annual flower show going on that time when we went, so yes we got lucky to witness that iconic thing, there were some nice food stalls all over the place selling sev puri, pani puri, bhel puri etc., which was good, Overall a very great experience must visit if you are in Bengaluru and love nature.

title: Trip to birds of paradise
content: So it was one of my best experiences in bengaluru where I got to spend time in nature's lap, watching birds and animals, closely, like I could take them in my hand, feed food to them, and observe them do their daily tasks. There were mostly exotic breeds of birds, their eggs and there was a reptiles section too. My friend was scared to take a snake in his hand even though non-poisonous. We had to book tickets before hand and had to reach right on time, we took bus from our home in hsr and later at agara we had to take a cab. While coming back we explored art of living which is in the same route where we had good satvik food too. Overall a great experience, I must say!
verification_feedback: The entry is relevant and seems authentic. The description matches the photo context of holding a reptile (turtle). title: Painting workshop by little boto
content: I went to Little Boto Art workshop with my friend, it was a weekend. I cam across this event through event brite, so we registered as we are inclined towards art and craft. We were given stencils on which we had to paint with colors of our choice, there were so may mediums of colors, like sketch pens, water color, pencil colors, crayons, pastel colors. We enjoyed this activity a lot, it freshened up our childhood memories. I would love to go more on such workshops.

title: Amazing Day at Cubbon Park
content: I visited cubbon park on a weekday morning, it was a beautiful sunny day, could see cherry blossoms in the park, as it was summer season. We had a nice walk in the park and felt a vibrant energy in the lap of nature. The air was fresh as it has greenery all around and a peaceful vibe. Great experience to go in morning
